def: The state or quality of being needy; want; poverty; indigence.
A house, inclosure, large cage, or other place, for keepingbirds confined; a bird house.Lincolnshire may be termed the aviary of England. Fuller.
Pertaining to, or of the nature of, a preface; introductory toa book, essay, or discourse; as, prefatory remarks.That prefatory addition to the Creed. Dryden.
Of or pertaining to Modena or its inhabitants.-- n. sing. & pl.
Of, pertaining to, or designating, a hypothetical sulphacid ofphosphorus, analogous to phosphoric acid, and known in its salts.
A yellow crystalline substance, C10H6O2, analogous to quinone,obtained by oxidizing naphthalene with chromic acid.
An order of Anthozoa; the Actinaria.
To happen ill or unluckily. Spenser.
